            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "Troops of baboons are led by dominant males, who use vocalizations, displays, and physical aggression to maintain their status within the group."
            },
            {
              "cf": "",
              "x": "Female baboons typically give birth to a single offspring after a gestation period of around six months, with infants clinging to their mother's fur for protection."
